sentences: Kirk P. Kelly (born circa 1960) is a folk singer, songwriter and labor activist from New York City.
Kelly's music has been infrequently recorded over the years.
A decade or so after starting his musical career Kelly was accepted to and attended an AFL-CIO organizer's training school and began working throughout the United States as a union organizer.
